A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the International WeLoveU Foundation; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the International WeLoveU Foundation, an NGO established in 2001, has been
4 associated with the United Nations Department of Global Communications since 2018; and
5 WHEREAS, WeLoveU's Founder and Chairwoman Zahng Gil-jah has inspired nearly
6 300,000 volunteers across more than 50 countries to serve their communities in six key areas:
7 Education, Emergency Relief, Environmental Protection, Health, International Aid, and
8 Social Welfare; and
9 WHEREAS, in January 2021, WeLoveU launched a National Blood Donation Campaign to
10 address the urgent need for blood caused by the COVID-19 pandemic, helping to save lives
11 across the United States; and
12 WHEREAS, on Sunday, September 15, 2024, volunteers from the WeLoveU Foundation
13 Southeast USA hosted a life-saving blood drive at Mercedes-Benz Stadium in collaboration
14 with the American Red Cross alongside simultaneous blood drives in Los Angeles,
15 California, and Philadelphia, Pennsylvania; and
